Rating: 4
Based on feedback from another reviewer, I used soy sourcream (don't eat dairy), instead of mayo. I also eliminated the sautee step with the chicken. I sauteed the scallions and then added the rest. If the breadcrumbs are a bit dry, you can add a little more olive oil. Then I just spread the sauce on top, added the breadcrumbs, and baked it. I did use chicken cutlets, which cuts down on the baking time. My guests, for whom I've cooked often, raved and thought it was one of the best things I've ever made. Not difficult or time consuming at all.

