I made a big pile of ths dish for a family gathering. It's an easy and versatile recipe, and you don't even have to measure any of the stuff in it--great for making larger batches. I love horseradish, so I used considerably more than recommended. Taking the suggestion of another reviewer, I used light sour cream instead of mayo. One thing you may have to do though, is broil the dish for a few extra minutes so that the bread crumbs get brown. I served it with steamed string beans and Israeli cous cous with mushromms and onions, and the meal got rave reviews!

Rating: 4
Ohhhh, I love this!! 3 forks as written, 4 forks with my modifications below. I already know I will be making this many, many times in the future. It's too easy and yet tastes so good! I use skinless breasts. Yes, there is tons of mayo to spread on, but it is important in retaining moisture; I prefer to replace it with fat-free sour cream. On a lazier day, I will try Dijonnaise. Like another reviewer, I browned the skinless chicken for 3 mins/side. And Pam works fine instead of oil. Like another reviewer, I prefer a stronger flavor. I increase the Dijon to 2.25 t and the horseradish to 3 T. I also double the scallions, garlic, and tarragon. Finally, I remove the skillet from the heat source before adding the garlic so it won't burn.

