Rating: 3
This is a favorite recipe of ours. However, we have made the following changes. I use boneless skinless breasts. I only cook the breasts for 3min on each side. I add about a teaspoon more olive oil when I sauté the scallions, this compensates for the extra grease the chicken skin would have added. I also do not use as much mayo & mustard I just put a thin coat on each breast. I also use good quality canned whole wheat bread crumbs I have also used plain old canned bread crumbs. We typically serve this dish with garlic mashed potatoes & peas.

